9930169d02c87f9dc8191b960ae70960460d0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"af0f7c3f","parentId":"bf8bde05","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:09:29.482Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_BAqVQx6s9161KlTL4dIe0lH1|fc_0bec8cc91ee6e9930169d02c8983f081919aaf0140a654cc7e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nThe filesystem is the ONLY communication channel between the boundary workflow\nand the OpenClaw agents. No sockets. No IPC. No shared memory. Just files.\n\n### Checkpoint Files\n\n| Checkpoint | Written By | Meaning |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| `b2_bootstrap_ready.json` | b2_director | Director has loaded the bootstrap contract and is ready |\n| `s3_requested.json` | b2_director | Director is requesting S3 visual planning to begin |\n| `s3_completed.json` | sm_s3_visual_planning | SM finished all S3 operators and compiled artefacts |\n| `b2_completed.json` | b2_director | Director has closed the block (all sectors done) |\n\n### Checkpoint Directory Structure\n\n```\ndata/{account}_{lang}/{video}/b2/\n  checkpoints/\n    b2_bootstrap_ready.json\n    s3_requested.json\n    s3_completed.json\n    b2_completed.json\n  sectors/\n    s3_visual_planning/\n      inputs/\n      operators/\n      compiled/\n      dispatch/\n```\n\n### Polling Implementation\n\n```python\nimport time\n\ndef poll_checkpoints(\n    cp_dir: Path,\n    target_checkpoints: list[str],\n    max_duration: int = 1800,\n    poll_interval: int = 5,\n) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"Poll for checkpoint files. Returns the first one found.\"\"\"\n    start = time.time()\n    while (time.time() - start) < max_duration:\n        for cp_name in target_checkpoints:\n            cp_path = cp_dir / cp_name\n            if cp_path.exists():\n                time.sleep(2)  # settle -- file may still be writing\n                return cp_name\n        time.sleep(poll_interval)\n    return None  # timeout\n```\n\n### Critical Rules:\n\n- **Disk is the ONLY source of truth** -- never rely on process exit codes\n- **Process exit code is NOT reliable** -- OpenClaw CLI returns 1 even on success sometimes\n- **Always add 2s settle time** after detecting a checkpoint (file may still be flushed)\n- **NEVER stop polling just because the CLI process died** -- the agent may have written the checkpoint before the CLI wrapper crashed\n- **Process death does NOT mean failure** -- always check for the checkpoint file first\n\n---\n\n## 6. Contract Shapes\n\nContracts are the JSON payloads that bootstrap agents and communicate between phases.\nEvery field must use **absolute paths** (no relative paths, ever).\n\n### b2.bootstrap.v1\n\nWritten by the boundary workflow to start the director.\n\n```json\n{\n    \"kind\": \"b2_start\",\n    \"contract_version\": \"b2.bootstrap.v1\",\n    \"job_id\": \"job_006_pt_1711900000\",\n    \"run_root\": \"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/data/006_pt/video_001\",\n    \"b2_root\": \"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/data/006_pt/video_001/b2\",\n    \"account_id\": \"006\",\n    \"language\": \"pt\",\n    \"inputs\": {\n        \"screenplay_analysis_path\": \"C:/.../data/006_pt/video_001/w1/screenplay_analysis.json\"\n    },\n    \"mode\": \"s3_only\"\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `kind` | Yes | Always `\"b2_start\"` |\n| `contract_version` | Yes | Always `\"b2.bootstrap.v1\"` |\n| `job_id` | Yes | Unique per run: `job_{account}_{lang}_{timestamp}` |\n| `run_root` | Yes | Absolute path to video directory |\n| `b2_root` | Yes | Absolute path to `{run_root}/b2` |\n| `account_id` | Yes | Account number (e.g., `\"006\"`) |\n| `language` | Yes | ISO 639-1 code (e.g., `\"pt\"`) |\n| `inputs.screenplay_analysis_path` | Yes | Absolute path to W1 output |\n| `mode` | No | `\"s3_only\"` for narrow testing, omit for full block |\n\n### b2.resume.v1\n\nWritten by the boundary workflow to resume the director after a sector completes.\n\n```json\n{\n    \"kind\": \"b2_resume\",\n    \"contract_version\": \"b2.resume.v1\",\n    \"run_root\": \"C:/.../data/006_pt/video_001\",\n    \"b2_root\": \"C:/.../data/006_pt/video_001/b2\",\n    \"reason\": \"s3_completed\",\n    \"trigger_artifact\": \"C:/.../b2/checkpoints/s3_completed.json\"\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `reason` | Yes | Which sector completed: `\"s3_completed\"`, `\"s4_completed\"`, etc. |\n| `trigger_artifact` | Yes | Absolute path to the completed checkpoint JSON |\n\nThe director reads `trigger_artifact` to discover the paths to compiled artefacts.\nIt must NOT hardcode artefact paths.\n\n### s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1\n\nWritten by the director (inside `s3_requested.json`) and consumed by the SM.\n\n```json\n{\n    \"kind\": \"s3_start\",\n    \"contract_version\": \"s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1\",\n    \"job_id\": \"job_006_pt_1711900000\",\n    \"sector_root\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning\",\n    \"source_package_path\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/inputs/s3_source_package.json\",\n    \"checkpoints_dir\": \"C:/.../b2/checkpoints\",\n    \"operators_dir\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/operators\",\n    \"compiled_dir\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/compiled\",\n    \"dispatch_dir\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/dispatch\"\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `sector_root` | Yes | Root of this sector's workspace |\n| `source_package_path` | Yes | The consolidated input data for this sector |\n| `checkpoints_dir` | Yes | Where the SM writes `s3_completed.json` |\n| `operators_dir` | Yes | Where operator outputs land |\n| `compiled_dir` | Yes | Where the SM writes compiled/merged artefacts |\n| `dispatch_dir` | Yes | Where operator dispatch JSONs are written |\n\n---\n\n## 7. What DOES NOT Work (Lessons Learned)\n\nThese failures were discovered in production. Do not repeat them.\n\n### DO NOT use:\n\n| Anti-pattern | What happens |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `subprocess.run()` for OpenClaw | Blocks the boundary workflow. On timeout, kills the process mid-write, corrupting checkpoints |\n| `ACP/sessions_spawn` as primary invocation | Not supported in webchat/Nerve environments. CLI exec is the only universal path |\n| Accumulated sessions (no cleanup) | Context bloat: 50k+ tokens of stale data, agents confuse videos, costs spike |\n| Hardcoded artefact paths in director | Breaks when directory structure changes. Director must read paths from checkpoint JSON |\n| Default timeout (600s) | Multi-operator flows routinely take 10-15 minutes. 600s causes premature termination |\n| `PIPE` for stdout/stderr | OS pipe buffer (4-64KB) fills up, deadlocks the child process silently |\n| Non-ASCII in directory names | Em dashes, accented chars, special symbols break CLI argument parsing on Windows |\n| Checking process exit code for success | OpenClaw CLI returns exit code 1 even on successful completions |\n\n### DO use:\n\n[182 more lines in file. Use offset=340 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775250569470}}
