{"type":"message","id":"3edc90a4","parentId":"089c9d74","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:09:38.506Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_t8lpDhq5g9R9x2fFzEG8DNpY|fc_0bec8cc91ee6e9930169d02c91d65081919f198b14be500622","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Requires\n\n- W1 complete (`screenplay_analysis.json`)\n- OpenClaw gateway running\n- `b2_director`, `sm_s3_visual_planning`, and 4 `op_s3_*` agents registered in OpenClaw\n\n## Output\n\n```\nb2/\n├── b2_bootstrap.json\n├── b2_resume.json\n├── state/b2_state.json\n├── checkpoints/\n│   ├── b2_bootstrap_ready.json\n│   ├── s3_requested.json\n│   ├── s3_completed.json\n│   └── b2_completed.json\n└── sectors/s3_visual_planning/\n    ├── inputs/s3_source_package.json\n    ├── s3_supervisor_bootstrap.json\n    ├── dispatch/*.json (4 operator dispatches)\n    ├── operators/*/output.json (4 operator outputs)\n    ├── compiled/\n    │   ├── compiled_entities.json\n    │   └── s3_sector_report.md\n    └── checkpoints/\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n- **Processes dying**: Use `nohup`+`disown`, check `--timeout`\n- **Session accumulation**: Run cleanup, check Nerve for token counts\n- **Wrong path (legacy)**: Ensure no agent references `auto_content_factory_legacy`\n- **Director can't find artefacts**: It reads paths from `s3_completed.json`, not hardcoded\n- **SM doing work internally instead of dispatching**: Check `OPERATIONS.md` instructs CLI dispatch\n\n## Production Results (2026-04-03)\n\n- Account: 006-pt, 150 scenes\n- 4 operators all invoked via CLI\n- Total time: ~8 minutes\n- Status: completed\n\n## Files Involved\n\n- `pipeline/workflows/w3_block2.py`\n- `pipeline/contracts/w3_output.py`\n- `pipeline/shared/utils/config_loader.py`\n- OpenClaw agents: `b2_director`, `sm_s3_visual_planning`, `op_s3_*`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775250578497}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e1083b3","parentId":"3edc90a4","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:09:41.286Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0bec8cc91ee6e9930169d02c944db48191963a95cb98f1b7cf\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp0CyVtW8Ez2nqCx8SJwe0HCkmcrTRbm1OgaIOdCS6SwtG8ZPR12Sy_XzX67Yq4-8xdo8zrDQwVymZmmuYYOblj1pQ_4mIB8Ie_zpX62k_pDUie9gY2PvoO2B2B_Nok8Zw75TCasIJcWCpU_IQwkQgT5RBB7804TlPFzCX4PHQTyvaw9aaGO0IVmW54lBh8keHEyMEAcEjIzNczMnWDcT2cvVHhByTcf4S9-na-PuIW4tTJTAprSVitwUUA2kFNAW59a6V90NqD3v4zjBsJ52wqZUwWeUKsnEH-esNEtgrp2KsEQKD8MRS1kYLKmemqxGCFOBrQhC9CJSWWydtYXtzv6npcQF_vN__sVFPdQAxIm7E31NeOYge_J1RLr3Ysn4g-g3OH3fLqMeuHN-0Y1mEePQ6pWY11NPwc-Am14xhMivG-F28-bZFrpV391314sertk0brANISFfIxUOPYsocVBehJbpic-XD998fi1XlBN2A80tuly8XizF8F64zKC73x9tDe5B62lkDpSNP1Xj7xNthpcTOiZ5VMs89rIu-eTganl6jlDisSy7efdxF6RKxuMtF9FZ8_kWkPZIIv6XuNM9C5SOEMGPmIcZPZEjy4kwNwGs0js9Su5d5z83-OJpM77kT5regvwi5AIdrNpX-KJlJrbyFm3MLYylUeio-79swCv8fE6m2-BPKq9uuyaBmdjIB0AgGC7OK0dodnFFoXjKaP9aN3qQKngEllw0m7ofFg-7sBuVBDFtmhobJvrxmzcn57OAa3_sl3nNUC_xK4_3-LLoE1WggT-1o6nnNZ1jBIhG3pnfM4FLbzMYhoL8PmyjH-5MTI645eTNnMD_J9R2ar9iiumipqpmu0R7ihy8dUDFKYqrVf8S_-Y3wmjOPogd7qh4eFmtS-3jyV4ok4MiLuT7oMfv9qx9SQqN2ewlRcnw=\",\"summary\":[]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_qEvSi345yhXRWfDgERJa1ZCt|fc_0bec8cc91ee6e9930169d02c952ee88191acf37637cee40847","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\openclaw_integration.md","offset":290,"limit":80},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\openclaw_integration.md\",\"offset\":290,\"limit\":80}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":628,"output":75,"cacheRead":23552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24255,"cost":{"input":0.0015700000000000002,"output":0.0011250000000000001,"cacheRead":0.005888,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008583}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775250578507,"responseId":"resp_0bec8cc91ee6e9930169d02c9326cc81918b14a77ddbaacce2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5653186","parentId":"8e1083b3","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:09:41.540Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_qEvSi345yhXRWfDgERJa1ZCt|fc_0bec8cc91ee6e9930169d02c952ee88191acf37637cee40847","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The director reads `trigger_artifact` to discover the paths to compiled artefacts.\nIt must NOT hardcode artefact paths.\n\n### s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1\n\nWritten by the director (inside `s3_requested.json`) and consumed by the SM.\n\n```json\n{\n    \"kind\": \"s3_start\",\n    \"contract_version\": \"s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1\",\n    \"job_id\": \"job_006_pt_1711900000\",\n    \"sector_root\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning\",\n    \"source_package_path\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/inputs/s3_source_package.json\",\n    \"checkpoints_dir\": \"C:/.../b2/checkpoints\",\n    \"operators_dir\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/operators\",\n    \"compiled_dir\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/compiled\",\n    \"dispatch_dir\": \"C:/.../b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/dispatch\"\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `sector_root` | Yes | Root of this sector's workspace |\n| `source_package_path` | Yes | The consolidated input data for this sector |\n| `checkpoints_dir` | Yes | Where the SM writes `s3_completed.json` |\n| `operators_dir` | Yes | Where operator outputs land |\n| `compiled_dir` | Yes | Where the SM writes compiled/merged artefacts |\n| `dispatch_dir` | Yes | Where operator dispatch JSONs are written |\n\n---\n\n## 7. What DOES NOT Work (Lessons Learned)\n\nThese failures were discovered in production. Do not repeat them.\n\n### DO NOT use:\n\n| Anti-pattern | What happens |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `subprocess.run()` for OpenClaw | Blocks the boundary workflow. On timeout, kills the process mid-write, corrupting checkpoints |\n| `ACP/sessions_spawn` as primary invocation | Not supported in webchat/Nerve environments. CLI exec is the only universal path |\n| Accumulated sessions (no cleanup) | Context bloat: 50k+ tokens of stale data, agents confuse videos, costs spike |\n| Hardcoded artefact paths in director | Breaks when directory structure changes. Director must read paths from checkpoint JSON |\n| Default timeout (600s) | Multi-operator flows routinely take 10-15 minutes. 600s causes premature termination |\n| `PIPE` for stdout/stderr | OS pipe buffer (4-64KB) fills up, deadlocks the child process silently |\n| Non-ASCII in directory names | Em dashes, accented chars, special symbols break CLI argument parsing on Windows |\n| Checking process exit code for success | OpenClaw CLI returns exit code 1 even on successful completions |\n\n### DO use:\n\n| Pattern | Why |\n|---------|-----|\n| `Popen` fire-and-forget + checkpoint polling | Non-blocking, resilient to CLI crashes |\n| CLI exec (`openclaw agent --agent X --message Y --json`) | Universal, works everywhere |\n| Session cleanup before every run | Prevents context pollution |\n| `--timeout 1800` on all invocations | Sufficient for multi-operator flows |\n| `--session-id` unique per run+phase+agent | Prevents session reuse |\n| `nohup + disown` when running from background tasks | Prevents SIGHUP killing the process |\n| ASCII-only directory names | Sanitize with `video_dir.py` helper |\n| 2-second settle time after checkpoint detection | File may still be flushing to disk |\n\n---\n\n## 8. How to Add a New Sector (S4/S5/S6)\n\nEvery sector follows the exact same boundary pattern. Here is the step-by-step checklist.\n\n### Step 1: Create OpenClaw Agents\n\nCreate the supervisor and operators in `~/.openclaw/agents/`:\n\n```\nsm_s4_{sector_name}/\n  agent.yaml          # system prompt, model config\n  sessions/\n\nop_s4_{operator_a}/\n  agent.yaml\n  sessions/\n\n[152 more lines in file. Use offset=370 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775250581527}}
